Highlights of the titles in the Volumes Series are Subversive Activities Investigation (Investigatory Hearings of the New York Department of Labor's Industrial Commission), 1941; Master Reference on Communism;
Communist Perspective: A Handbook of Communist Doctrinal Statements in the Original Russian and English;
Communism in the Motion Picture Industry; Joint Statement of Five Employees of Allis Chalmers Manufacturing Company Before the House of Representatives Committee on Education and Labor, 1947; and works of J.B. Matthews: Odyssey of a Fellow Traveler and Guinea Pigs No More. In this series are two reports published by John A. Clements Associates: Report on Venezuela (1958) and Report on Guatemala (1952). A mimeographed report, Vanguard in Guatemala - The Myth Comes to America, used by J.B. and Ruth I. Matthews for Report on Guatemala is in the Addresses and Writings Series.

